Example
Rename a file on the FTP server:
<?php
// connect and login to FTP server
$ftp_server = "ftp.example.com";
$ftp_conn = ftp_connect($ftp_server) or die("Could not connect to $ftp_server");
$login = ftp_login($ftp_conn, $ftp_username, $ftp_userpass);
$old_file = "oldfile.txt";
$new_file = "newfile.txt";
// try to rename $old_file to $new_file
if (ftp_rename($ftp_conn, $old_file, $new_file))
{
echo "Renamed $old_file to $new_file";
}
else
{
echo "Problem renaming $old_file to $new_file";
}
// close connection
ftp_close($ftp_conn);
?>
Definition and Usage
The ftp_rename() function renames a file or directory on the FTP server.
Syntax
ftp_rename(
ftp_conn, oldname, newname
);
Parameter Values
Parameter
Description
ftp_conn
Required. Specifies the FTP connection to use
oldname
Required. Specifies the file or directory to rename
newname
Required. Specifies the new name of the file or directory
Technical Details
Return Value:
TRUE on success, FALSE on failure
PHP Version:
4+

